ure dominance  rf sim on the  ghz band versus nfc on the  mhz band this survey attempts to provide an overview of the contactless mobile payments ecosystem in china it also explores the nearterm regulatory directives and the payment technology competition amongst the key players and points out the likely winners the race to lead in china primarily exists among the mnos banking institutions and the third party mobile payment service providers each has its own competitive advantage and offering to consumers mobile payments in china nfc rf sim and simpass q   research report report  rrapmm   pages   tables   charts   figures    download table of contents document summary china is the world’s largest single mobile market indeed china’s mobile payments industry is a burgeoning market it is attracting a number of participants in an attempt to assume first mover advantage while the market potential is very real there is uncertainty over which proximity payment technology will ultimately secure dominance  rf sim on the  ghz band versus nfc on the  mhz band this survey attempts to provide an overview of the contactless mobile payments ecosystem in china it also explores the nearterm regulatory directives and the payment technology competition amongst the key players and points out the likely winners the race to lead in china primarily exists among the mnos banking institutions and the third party mobile payment service providers each has its own competitive advantage and offering to consumers table of contents drivers executive summary scope and technology issues payment technologies proximity technologies in china the china market market size market drivers challenges and constraints china mobile payment ecosystem regulators financial service and telecommunication players supporting stakeholders key industry players china mobile china unicom china telecom china unionpay nxp gemalto shanghai fudan microelectronics hengbao watchdata directel holdings ltd hunan hisun mobile pa