hone services include one card multiple number service and hong kong local mobile phone services the group also provides telesales dealership services and other services reporting period and scope the reporting period of this report covers the financial year of  from  january  to  december  which is the same as the reporting period of the groups annual report for the year ended  december  the subject of this report is directel holdings limited and its major subsidiaries the principal place of business is the office of the group in hong kong sources of information the information disclosed in this report is mainly sourced from internal files of the company and public information in the market all information contents have been reviewed and confirmed by the management and overseeing departments of the company should you have queries or opinions on any contents of this report please do not hesitate to contact our company secretary andrew li via email infodirectelhk or phone    environmental social and governance report  environment‌‌ environment related policies the group is a mobile virtual network operator the board of directors also acknowledges well the importance of performing as a responsible corporate citizen the group has been implementing environmental protection and energy saving measures where practicable to improve the efficiency of resources consumption in establishing internal policies the group has strictly complied with the relevant laws and regulations on environmental protection implemented by the government the group will review the workflow process and the execution of relevant measures from time to time to ensure consistent implementation of the relevant policies the working environment of the group is an indoor office located in hong kong without any industrial plants as such the business of the group does not generate any hazardous waste air emission and waste water directly the group responds to the initiative of green office in its daily business operations by improving the efficiency of resources consumption reducing waste generation through paper recycling etc use of resources the group strives to use resources effectively and minimize the discharge of wastes in the ordinary course of business we have gradually implemented various energy saving and emission reduction measures the relevant examples are as follows energy saving keep indoor airconditioning temperature at ˚c encourage staff to shut down computers after work and switch off the lights if the employees are expected to be away from the room for more than one hour encourage staff to switch office equipment such as printers and computers to energy saving mode the equipment will enter the sleep mode under the standby condition and replace the lighting system in the office by led lights gradually reduce the use of resources encourage doubleside printing and reuse of waste paper purchase green and environmental printing paper and encourage to use electronic channels for internal correspondence and communication as far as possible  directel holdings limited directel holdings limited published this content on  june  and is solely responsible for the information contained herein distributed by public unedited and unaltered on  june   utc original documenthttpwwwdirectelhkuploaddownloadepdf public permalinkhttpwwwpublicnowcomviewaedeeddafeffcca  latest news companies p tesla  shares rise as investors bet on model  success p citigroup  through serviceworks program citi employee finds the perfect opportunity to serve p legal notices  aug   p detection technology oyj  plc  managers transactions p deutsche asset management  reduces fees across suite of international mutual funds p athene holding ltd  announces flow reinsurance treaty with lincoln financial group p am best  revises outlooks to positive for international general insurance holdings limited and its subsidiaries p navient  employees donate more than  items to aid service members military veteran